# Loopany — environment. Copy to packages/server/.env (or set in your host / Fly secrets).

# --- database (Postgres) ---
# The server runs on Postgres. Two tiers, chosen by whether DATABASE_URL is set:
#
#  1. UNSET (default) → embedded, file-backed pglite at <LOOPANY_DATA_DIR>/pgdata.
#     Zero external database — this is the local-dev + light-self-host default,
#     migrates itself in-process at boot. `pnpm dev` just runs; the BUILT server
#     (`pnpm start` / Docker / Fly) additionally requires LOOPANY_DB=pglite as an
#     explicit opt-in - without it a missing DATABASE_URL fails the boot loudly
#     (so a lost prod secret can't silently boot an empty ephemeral database).
#  2. SET → postgres-js against your Postgres (e.g. Supabase). Point DATABASE_URL
#     at the TRANSACTION POOLER (:6543) — the driver forces prepare:false for
#     pgBouncer. Set DIRECT_DATABASE_URL to the DIRECT (:5432) session URL; ONLY
#     migrations use it (DDL + advisory lock must not go through the pooler).
#     Both URLs must carry ?sslmode=require for Supabase/any remote Postgres (TLS).
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://USER:PASS@HOST.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres?sslmode=require
# DIRECT_DATABASE_URL=postgresql://USER:PASS@HOST.supabase.com:5432/postgres?sslmode=require
# LOOPANY_DB=pglite   # opt the BUILT server into the embedded tier (see tier 1)

# --- data dir ---
# Server-side file state; also hosts the embedded pglite data dir (tier 1 above).
# Ignored by the hosted Postgres tier (tier 2). On Fly's pglite tier this is the volume.
# Defaults to ~/.loopany. Must be an ABSOLUTE path — the code does NOT expand `~`, so an
# uncommented `~/.loopany` here would create a literal ./~/.loopany directory.
# LOOPANY_DATA_DIR=/absolute/path

# --- artifact blob store (Cloudflare R2, S3-compatible) ---
# Where live-synced loop artifact BYTES are stored (metadata stays in Postgres).
# All four required vars unset ⇒ the store falls back to an in-memory impl
# (dev/test default — no creds, no network). Credentials are never hardcoded.
# LOOPANY_R2_ACCOUNT_ID=<cloudflare account id>   # used to derive the endpoint
# LOOPANY_R2_BUCKET=<bucket name>
# LOOPANY_R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID=<r2 access key>
# LOOPANY_R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=<r2 secret key>
# Optional. Endpoint defaults to https://<account id>.r2.cloudflarestorage.com.
# LOOPANY_R2_ENDPOINT=
# Optional. R2 ignores region; "auto" is its convention (the default).
# LOOPANY_R2_REGION=auto

# --- artifact storage retention / GC (see gateway/retention.ts) ---
# Knobs that bound blob storage growth. All read lazily at call time, each with a
# safe, generous default - leave unset unless you need to tune them.
# Per-loop total stored-bytes cap; the sync stops accepting NEW bytes for a loop
# once its live footprint reaches this (deletions/existing files still reconcile).
# Default 524288000 (500MB).
# LOOPANY_LOOP_BYTES_CAP=524288000
# How many of the most recent run snapshots to keep per loop (older ones pruned,
# which unpins their blobs for GC). Default 20.
# LOOPANY_SNAPSHOT_RETENTION=20
# Blob GC grace window: a blob whose metadata row is younger than this is never
# collected (concurrency guard). Default 3600000 (1 hour).
# LOOPANY_BLOB_GC_GRACE_MS=3600000
# How often the periodic storage-maintenance pass runs (prune snapshots → GC blobs).
# Default 900000 (15 minutes).
# LOOPANY_GC_INTERVAL_MS=900000

# --- server ---
# Dev port (vite). Prod (nitro) reads PORT.
LOOPANY_PORT=3000
LOOPANY_LOG_LEVEL=info
# Stuck-run reclaim: a claimed run that never reports is errored after this (ms).
# LOOPANY_RUN_TIMEOUT_MS=1200000
# Self-schedule cadence floors — enforced ONLY on the RUN self-schedule path (a
# run using set-cron / reschedule on itself); the owner's editLoop path is
# unlimited. Min minutes between adjacent fires a run may set via set-cron
# (default 15) and the soonest a run may reschedule itself (default 5).
# LOOPANY_SELF_CRON_FLOOR_MINUTES=15
# LOOPANY_SELF_RESCHEDULE_FLOOR_MINUTES=5
# Circuit breaker: auto-pause a loop after this many CONSECUTIVE exec failures
# (enabled=false + unscheduled, one calm note that subsumes the failure alert;
# re-enable to resume). Default 10; set 0 to disable. `skipped` runs are
# transparent to the streak - only phase `error` counts.
# LOOPANY_FAILURE_AUTOPAUSE_STREAK=10

# --- auth (Better Auth + GitHub). OFF when GITHUB_* are unset → app is open. ---
# GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=
# GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=
# Public base URL (OAuth callback origin), e.g. https://loopany.fly.dev
# LOOPANY_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:3000
# Session signing secret — set a long random value in prod.
# LOOPANY_AUTH_SECRET=
# Comma-separated emails allowed to sign in (empty = anyone allowed).
# LOOPANY_ALLOWED_LOGINS=you@example.com,teammate@example.com
# Comma-separated emails granted superadmin (cross-team visibility). Empty = none.
# LOOPANY_SUPERADMINS=you@example.com,teammate@example.com

# --- notifications ---
# Push channels are NOT configured via env. They are set up per team in the
# dashboard (the Notifications modal): Telegram and Feishu have add-forms today,
# and Slack is a supported delivery transport without a UI add-form yet. Each
# channel's secrets are stored server-side per team, and a loop routes to one.

# === Daemon (@crewlet/loopany, runs on each user's machine) ===
# LOOPANY_TOKEN=<device token shown when you add a machine in the UI>
# LOOPANY_SERVER_URL=http://127.0.0.1:3000   # or https://loopany.fly.dev
# LOOPANY_ROOTS=~/Workspace,~/notes          # cwd jail (empty = unrestricted)
# LOOPANY_POLL_MS=3000
# LOOPANY_CLAUDE_BIN=claude
# Coding-agent (claude) wall-clock timeout, ms. Opt-in override: a positive value
# arms the timer; unset/0/invalid/negative ⇒ unlimited (the default). A run that
# disappears is caught by the server's inactivity sweep, not this daemon timer.
# LOOPANY_EXEC_TIMEOUT_MS=900000
# Transient-failure resume: on a TRANSIENT claude crash (API error / connection
# closed / ECONNRESET / overloaded / rate limit / 5xx) the daemon retries via
# `claude --resume <sessionId>`. Auth/quota, poisoned, and task failures never
# retry; timeouts and aborts never retry. Max retries default 2 (set 0 to
# disable); backoff base default 15000ms (then 4x, jittered).
# LOOPANY_TRANSIENT_RETRIES=2
# LOOPANY_TRANSIENT_RETRY_BASE_MS=15000

# FLY_API_TOKEN=""
